om/fkiraly","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/fkiraly/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/fkiraly/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/fkiraly/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/fkiraly/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/fkiraly/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/fkiraly/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/fkiraly/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/fkiraly/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/fkiraly/received_events","type":"User","site_admin":false}},{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/sktime/sktime/issues/comments/646560212","html_url":"https://github.com/sktime/sktime/issues/265#issuecomment-646560212","issue_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/sktime/sktime/issues/265","id":646560212,"node_id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDY0NjU2MDIxMg==","user":{"login":"Mo-Saif","id":27867617,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjI3ODY3NjE3","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/27867617?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/Mo-Saif","html_url":"https://github.com/Mo-Saif","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/Mo-Saif/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/Mo-Saif/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/Mo-Saif/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/Mo-Saif/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/Mo-Saif/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/Mo-Saif/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/Mo-Saif/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/Mo-Saif/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/Mo-Saif/received_events","type":"User","site_admin":false},"created_at":"2020-06-19T10:24:00Z","updated_at":"2020-06-19T10:42:05Z","author_association":"CONTRIBUTOR","body":"Hi, I created a function that performs the task discussed here. Please feel free to modify it and add it sktime.\r\n```python\r\nimport pandas as pd\r\nfrom sktime.utils.data_container import detabularize\r\n\r\ndef read_univariate_ts(file, window_size, target_distance=1):\r\n    \"\"\"\r\n    Reads a univariate time-series csv file and converts it to sktime nested format.\r\n    \r\n    Parameters\r\n    ----------\r\n    file : str, path object or file-like object\r\n        pandas compatable path i.e:\r\n        Any valid string path is acceptable. The string could be a URL. Valid\r\n        URL schemes include http, ftp, s3, and file. For file URLs, a host is\r\n        expected. A local file could be: file://localhost/path/to/table.csv.\r\n\r\n        If you want to pass in a path object, pandas accepts any ``os.PathLike``.\r\n\r\n        By file-like object, we refer to objects with a ``read()`` method, such as\r\n        a file handler (e.g. via builtin ``open`` function) or ``StringIO``.\r\n    window_size : int\r\n        Number of historical values used in each prediction.\r\n    target_distance : int\r\n        The number of steps inthe future you want to predict.\r\n        \r\n    Returns\r\n    -------\r\n    X : pandas DataFrame\r\n        Nested DataFrame with window_size long pandas Series in each row\r\n    y : pandas Series\r\n        The target for each case in X\r\n    \"\"\"\r\n    \r\n    df = pd.read_csv(file)\r\n    y = df.shift(-target_distance)\r\n    \r\n    lagslist = []\r\n    for i in range(window_size-1, -1, -1):\r\n        lagslist.append(df.shift(i))\r\n        \r\n    X = pd.concat(lagslist, axis =1)\r\n    X = X.iloc[window_size-1:-target_distance]\r\n    X = detabularize(X)\r\n    y = y.iloc[window_size-1:-target_distance].squeeze(axis=1)\r\n    \r\n    return X, y\r\n```","reactions":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/sktime/sktime/issues/comments/646560212/reactions","total_count":1,"+1":1,"-1":0,"laugh":0,"hooray":0,"confused":0,"heart":0,"roc